Nsync - Nsync [1998]
	



*NSYNC is the 1998 self-titled debut album by the boy band 'N Sync, released in the United States on March 24, 1998. At first, album sales were mediocre until *NSYNC's 1998 Summer Disney Concert. After the concert was aired, sales began to sky rocket. It reached #2 on the chart and has shipped over 10 million copies in the US alone, making it certified 10x Platinum and earning the group a RIAA diamond award. It won a Teen Choice award in 1999 for Album of The Year.
